Pergament, 114 ff., ca. 15,8 × 11 cm; 9. årh.
Håndskriftet har tilhørt Friedrich Lindenbrog (1573-1648) og indgik sammen med adskillige andre af dennes håndskrifter i biblioteket på Gottorp Slot. Siden blev det en del af den betydelige håndskriftsamling, som bibliotekaren på Gottorp Marquard Gude (1635-1689) erhvevede sig privat, og det blev på den ikke fuldførte auktion over dennes håndskrifter i Hamburg 1706 erhvervet af filologen Johann Albert Fabricius (1668-1736). Dennes håndskriftsamling forvaredes siden af svigersønnen Hermann Samuel Reimarus, efter hvis død i 1768 den erhvervedes af Københavns Universitetsbibliotek i 1770. Alle Universitetsbibliotekets håndskrifter overførtes i 1938 til Det Kongelige Bibliotek

Parchment, 114 ff., ca. 15,8 × 11 cm; 9th century
The manuscript was acquired by Friedrich Lindenbrog (1573-1648) in 1603. Together with several others of his manuscripts it was handed over to the ducal library at Gottorp Castle. Later it occurred in the private library of Marquard Gude (1635-1689), who was for a period librarian at Gottorp. It was acquired by Johann Albert Fabricius (1668-1736) at the only partially completed auction of Gude's manuscripts in Hamburg 1706. Fabricius' manuscript collection was inherited by his son-in-law Hermann Samuel Reimarus, after whose death in 1768 it was bought as an ensemble by Copenhagen University Library in 1770. The entire University Library collection of manuscripts was incorporated into the Royal Library in 1938
